<% content_for(:title) { "How To: Emoji &bull; Help-QA.com".html_safe } %>

<h1>Emoji</h1>
<p>Emoji's can be searched by typing a colon <code>:</code> and the emoji name. An autocomplete field will pop up that you can use to select an emoji.</p>
<p>Use the "Quick Search" area below to search for an emoji.</p>

<input type="text" autofocus="true" autocomplete="off" placeholder="Quick Search" class="emoji-quick-search">

<div class="emoji-loader">
  <% @emoji_list.each do |emoji_name, aliases| %>
    <% code, raw_emoji = emoji_name.split(",") %>
    <div class="searchable-container" data-type="emoji" data-searchable-by="<%= aliases %>">
      <div class="emoji-wrapper"><%= raw_emoji %></div>
      <div class="aliases"><%= aliases.split(" ").join(", ") %></div>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
